[l] OMGWTF-Meldung der Woche:Economists have long struggled to explain why a growing proportion of men in the prime of their lives are not employed or looking for work. A new study has found that nearly half of these men are on painkillers and many are disabled.Fuer einen Amerika-Reisenden ist das nicht ueberraschend mit den Painkillern. Aber die Groessenordnung mal in Zahlen zu hoeren, das ist ja schon noch mal was anderes.As of last month, 11.4 percent of men between the ages of 25 and 54 — or about seven million people — were not in the labor force, which means that they were not employed and were not seeking a job.
